devdoc.details: This interface can be used for listening to the updates for off-chain and testing purposes.

BatchPriceFeedUpdate(uint16,uint64).details: Emitted when a batch price update is processed successfully.

params.chainId: ID of the source chain that the batch price update comes from.
params.sequenceNumber: Sequence number of the batch price update.

PriceFeedUpdate(bytes32,uint64,int64,uin.details: Emitted when the price feed with `id` has received a fresh update.

params.conf: Confidence interval of the given price update.
params.price: Price of the given price update.
params.publishTime: Publish time of the given price update.

devdoc.title: IPythEvents contains the events that Pyth contract emits.
